From b414074ee6ad911ca0f79ac31b6e5e70a6edc371 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 14:46:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 170/174] mm/huge_memory: fix file-PMD-THP MM_FILEPAGES rss
 leak under PGCL

__split_huge_pmd_locked()'s present-folio PMD teardown subtracted
HPAGE_PMD_NR from MM_FILEPAGES, but under page clustering MM_FILEPAGES rss
is MMUPAGE-granular and the file-PMD-THP fault adds +HPAGE_PMD_MMUNR
(== HPAGE_PMD_NR << PAGE_MMUSHIFT).  Tearing down a 2MB file THP thus
returned only the cluster count (HPAGE_PMD_NR) of the sub-PTE count
(HPAGE_PMD_MMUNR) it had added, leaking (PAGE_MMUCOUNT-1)/PAGE_MMUCOUNT of
each PMD's MM_FILEPAGES.  With transparent_hugepage=always (Fedora default)
every process that mmaps files leaks file rss -> "BUG: Bad rss-counter
state ... type:MM_FILEPAGES val:~970000" at exit (reproduced for the test
workload AND systemd-journald).  The sibling migration-entry path and
zap_huge_pmd() already use HPAGE_PMD_MMUNR.

QEMU A/B (pgcl4 DEBUG_VM, THP=always, MADV_COLLAPSE file reproducer):
unfixed 9 Bad-rss-counter records / fixed 0.  Identity at PAGE_MMUSHIFT==0.
Reproducer: pgcl userspace/file_collapse_repro.c.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01UkhHXA2PvPb3uwymHGbYh8
---
 mm/huge_memory.c | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/huge_memory.c b/mm/huge_memory.c
index f937b7e11aa9..c109551ee8d3 100644
--- a/mm/huge_memory.c
+++ b/mm/huge_memory.c
@@ -3133,7 +3133,14 @@ static void __split_huge_pmd_locked(struct vm_area_struct *vma, pmd_t *pmd,
 			if (!folio_test_referenced(folio) && pmd_young(old_pmd))
 				folio_set_referenced(folio);
 			folio_remove_rmap_pmd(folio, page, vma);
-			add_mm_counter(mm, mm_counter_file(folio), -HPAGE_PMD_NR);
+			/*
+			 * PGCL: MM_FILEPAGES rss is MMUPAGE-granular and the
+			 * file-PMD-THP fault adds +HPAGE_PMD_MMUNR, so tear-down
+			 * must subtract HPAGE_PMD_MMUNR, not the cluster-count
+			 * HPAGE_PMD_NR (which leaks the rest of the PMD per split).
+			 * Matches the migration path below + zap_huge_pmd().
+			 */
+			add_mm_counter(mm, mm_counter_file(folio), -HPAGE_PMD_MMUNR);
 			folio_put(folio);
 			return;
 		}
